g.text: research cannot determine the exact extent to which
the ventilation system or informational campaign led
to reduction in PACU airborne contaminants, the
overall result suggests both were successful.
The research led to recommendations for
Rajavithi Hospital. First, the hospital should continue
training and informing its PACU and other workers on
the importance of all health and safety procedures. A
compliance office may be of assistance in ensuring best
practices. Second, the hospital should continue
monitoring and measuring its air quality in the PACU,
including testing for all anesthetic gases, and with the
aim of identifying the specific strands of bacteria and
fungi present. Also, the hospital should adjust the current
ventilation system such that concentrations of pollutants
fall within RELs, or the hospital should improve the
ventilation system through additional purchases or
remodeling of the PACU. Finally, the hospital should
partner with officials from Ministry of Health and other
hospitals to spearhead a campaign designed to help
other hospitals in the Thai health system achieve proper
hygiene in their PACU environments. Through continued
